<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Solidago</i> <i>canadensis</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Agrostis</i> <i>scabra</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>athrostachya</i>, <i>Deschampsia</i> <i>cespitosa</i>, <i>Horkelia</i> <i>fusca</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>primuloides</i>, <i>Poa</i> <i>pratensis</i>, <i>Potentilla</i> <i>gracilis</i> and <i>Trifolium</i> spp. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1.5 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Montane meadows, forest margins. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Solidago canadensis</i> as a FACU plant. </div>
</div>

		
